          "author": 0,
          "author_avatar_urls": {
            "24": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/916b8cf5ecc66a23edc79c45cf2fc6817f0b5424081e70f0a71c2cf53a043285?s=24&r=g",
            "48": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/916b8cf5ecc66a23edc79c45cf2fc6817f0b5424081e70f0a71c2cf53a043285?s=48&r=g",
            "96": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/916b8cf5ecc66a23edc79c45cf2fc6817f0b5424081e70f0a71c2cf53a043285?s=96&r=g"
          },
          "author_name": "gbe0",
          "author_url": "https://gbe0.com",
          "content": {
            "rendered": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>In your export policy, did you try using a prefix-list-filter with exact match instead? A prefix filter alone will allow more specific routes.</p>\n<p>Eg.</p>\n<p>set policy-statement as6453-v4-out term prefixes-out from prefix-list-filter as48635-v4 exact</p>\n<p>Then remove the existing prefix-list from the term.</p>\n"
          },
          "date": "2023-03-29T11:20:32",
          "id": 126,
          "link": "https://www.daryllswer.com/navigating-a-bgp-zombie-outbreak-on-juniper-routers/#comment-126",
